  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2004-07-22",
    "date": "2004-09-02T19:37:44Z",
    "text": "Closing the Coverage Gap Act of 2004 - Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act, as amended by the Medicare Prescription Drug, Improvement, and Modernization Act of 2003, to eliminate: (1) the initial standard prescription drug coverage limit of $2,250 (adjusted for inflation); and (2) the MedicareAdvantage regional plan stabilization fund.\n\nRepeals the Premium Support Demonstration Program.\n\nEliminates Health Savings Accounts under the Medicare Prescription Drug, Improvement, and Modernization Act of 2003."
  },
